# grapher_aspect_line_smoke.numos — Phase 10C. Plot y=x at the default (now
# equal-aspect) view. On a square grid y=x must render at a visual 45 degrees,
# which is the simplest proof that 1 unit in x equals 1 unit in y in pixels.
# Also exercises trace (ENTER) on an explicit function without crashing.
# Warning-only (screenshot, no golden).
log "aspect line: start"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
key down
key enter
key y
key =
key x
key enter
wait 80
key graph
wait 80
# flush deferred first replot via a neutral nav key, then screenshot
key ac
key 0
wait 120
screenshot out/grapher_aspect_line_smoke.ppm
# exercise trace on an explicit function (must not crash)
key enter
wait 20
key right
key right
wait 40
assert_app Grapher
log "aspect line: y=x plotted + traced"
